The paper deals with the problem of facial landmark detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also utilizes deep learning models and adversarial attacks, which are common in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image manipulation, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the proposed method against attacks, which is related to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
